author: Collin Chan
text: Upgraded facilities and the lighting is much better. Probably good to revamp every 5 years Their social media posts are engaging. Kudos!

author: Sujoy Kapoor
text: I've been going to this gym for the last six months and always been welcomed by the team with a smile. There have been a few additions of certain gym equipment which is always good to see. It sometimes tends to get crowded so I try to go during non peak hours. I have had good experience with PT and the crowd in general so would definitely recommend.

author: unicorncutekate93
text: The place was renovated recently. There are shower and toilet facilities. Crowd here is friendly and the vibes are good for growth. I made some friends in the last month and the frequent members are friendly. Equipment is with great variety. The club staff are responsive and friendly too!

author: Judy Tan
text:
Nice and friendly gym users here. Didn‚Äôt have a good impression when I dropped by before reno. It‚Äôs a different story now. Not exactly a big space but there are so many machines and more than enough to go around. Gym users here are friendly too (I was zoning out after completing a set and noticed someone asking if I was waiting for the cable machine he had been using. He‚Äôs taking a break and willing to share. So sweet of him to even offer to share).

There‚Äôs just really little space for stretching or mat work though but it‚Äôs not much to complain about because those ones can be done at home anyways.

Cleaning auntie is also always on the move cleaning after everyone. She‚Äôs working as hard as we are.

Nice to workout here.

author: Zachary Adam Lim
text:
Recently renovated and it's great! Looks more refined and definitely feels like a breath of fresh air during your workout!
Big shout-out to the auntie janitor! She really maintains the gym very well and very friendly too!

author: Felicia Yap
text:
Have been training here weekly with my PT for nearly 2 months and it has been a pleasant journey. At the last training, when he requested to share weights with someone, the person refused even though the weights were on the floor, and not in use when my PT approached him. (this is one of the reasons why i am quite scared of gyms)

The gym is great (they recently added new machines even) and the manager is super approachable! but when there are unkind people like that, i am affected and i will dread seeing the same person again.

5 stars for the gym and no stars for the unkind soul. hopefully everyone can be kinder and make the gym a better place

author: J
text: I used to really enjoy this gym before the renovation. Yes, the environment has been renovated, but unfortunately the gym experience has gone downhill. Before renovation, it was much better ‚Äî you could actually train without constant waiting. Now it‚Äôs so overcrowded that most equipment is unusable during regular hours. The space looks new, but it‚Äôs practically useless if you can‚Äôt even work out properly. Very disappointing.

author: Jacynda Teo
text:
Fantastic Upgrade After Renovation!

I‚Äôve been a member at Midtown Anytime Fitness for a while, and the recent renovation in June 2025 has truly brought the gym to the next level! The space looks fresh, modern, and more inviting than ever.

What impressed me most was the addition of newer, high-quality machines ‚Äî everything feels smoother, more efficient, and user-friendly. From cardio to strength training equipment, you can really feel the difference. The layout is also more spacious and well-organised, which makes workouts feel less cramped even during peak hours.

Big thumbs up to the management for investing in this uplift. The gym has a great energy now, and it‚Äôs even more motivating to train here. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a well-maintained and well-equipped fitness space! üí™

author: Xclusive
text:
In the passed. I used to train without even thinking there is eyes looking at me. Now staff check this check that. This cannot wear, need to wear this. Cannot put your bag here. Hmm.. sounds like a parents talking to a kid. Years back don't have all these rules, just remember to pay your monthly membership. Come don't come, just pay. If come, no stress, just enjoy your workout.

Now make's me feel very uneasy. It's like going to a government gym. The difference, Government gym is cheaper and bigger.

In the passed, sure 5 star. Sorry now hard, need to share based on my experience. I seldom come this outlet anymore, unless no choice. Visit other outlet or sign contract with other place. Don't make yourself feel like me. Let's see, will check out other gym. Anyway here is small and stuffy

author: Weihong Huang
text: Well equipped and decent sized gym. Renovated quite recently. Has two decent sized toilet / showers rooms.

author: Hung Hao
text:
On my quest to review all anytime fitness outlets, I was quite pleasantly surprised by this outlet!

It‚Äôs well equipped with 4 treadmills, 3 elliptical and even 1 spin bike. I‚Äôm sure it more than fulfils your cardio requirements.

There‚Äôs also free weights (with dumbbells going heavy‚Ä¶ you won‚Äôt ever need to use them!). There‚Äôs 2 squat racks + 1 smith machine so do take note if you‚Äôre an avid squatter this might be a bit of a cramped space.

This place is well equipped with 2 rooms with shower + toilet in each one. Extra cookie points for the inbody body analysis machine that‚Äôs free for everyone to use.

I had fun with some speciality machine such as the biceps curl machine and tricep extension machine. Those are rare to come by and I thoroughly enjoyed using them.

Overall it‚Äôs pretty small, and I can definitely see how space can be a possible constrain when the crowd hits the gym. It is however, kept clean and well equipped. It is located at B1, with direct entry from carpark so I suppose it‚Äôs convenient for drivers.

author: Lennard
text: Very crowded gym. Staff threatened to ‚Äûforcefully remove you from the machine‚Äú, after kindly declining the question to share the machine with more than two people and insists on using the machine immediately. They were not willing to wait two minutes. I am scared of the ‚Äûpersonal trainers‚Äú taking testosterone and scare members if they don‚Äôt immediately get what they want. I avoid going to this gym. I raised the issue to Anytime Fitness management, where their first reaction was to not respond. The second reaction after raising it formally again, was trying to belittle. I am disappointed by how anytime fitness administration handles these kind of issues very unprofessionally and it‚Äôs honestly concerning how there was no action taken to address these issues at all.

The team have also been working hard the past 6 months or so, getting the aircon(?) cleaned for better air circulation, maintaining machines & benches, providing new attachments, listening to members feedback and more.

author: Jay Quellin
text:
I've been a member for almost two years, and I have to say, this is by far the worst outlet I‚Äôve ever been to. The equipment here is in terrible condition‚Äîworn out, outdated, and poorly maintained. It‚Äôs a struggle to get a decent workout in because everything just feels off.

The atmosphere is another major issue. There are absolutely no vibes in this place; it's eerily quiet, more like a library than a gym. The silence is unsettling, and it‚Äôs hard to stay motivated when you can hear your own thoughts echoing in the emptiness. There‚Äôs no energy, no music, nothing to get you pumped up for your workout.

To make matters worse, the place is a mess. Equipment is scattered everywhere, and it‚Äôs clear that cleanliness and organization are not priorities here. It‚Äôs frustrating to navigate through the clutter, and it really kills any momentum I try to build during my sessions.

I dislike this outlet so much that I couldn‚Äôt even focus on what I was doing. In the process of writing this review, I completely forgot to take my bottle with me as I was leaving‚Äîa small but telling sign of the frustration and hatred I have for this place.

Some ‚Äúseasoned‚Äù gym members also use the front admin desks as their own personal locker, placing their personal belongings everywhere, making the place look like a mess.
